<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 06 at 2:14PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Pike and northern
Lamar Counties through 245 PM EDT...
At 214 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Lifsey Springs, or near
Zebulon, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Barnesville, Zebulon, Milner, Williamson, Orchard Hill, Meansville,
Aldora, Liberty Hill, Hilltop, Lifsey Springs and Piedmont.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
